author: COMSOL
description: The thin low-permittivity gap boundary condition, which is available for electrostatic field modeling, approximates a thin layer of material with low relative permittivity compared to its surroundings. This example compares the thin low-permittivity gap boundary condition to a full-fidelity model and discusses the range of applicability of this boundary condition.
